window.ARCH_VANILLA_TOPIC_SEED = {
  "crazy_ecologist": {hello1:"Ah, a visitor! Do you know what a Moonlight does to your neural pathways at prolonged exposure? I do. Fourteen hours, thirty-seven minutes. The colors never went away — beautiful, actually. Welcome to my laboratory! Everything you see is perfectly organized... in my head, at least. Looking to trade? I know artifacts better than anyone alive. Possibly better than anyone dead, too.", hello2:"*muttering over instruments* ...crystalline lattice structure suggests a Kolobok variant, but the emission signature... Oh! You! Didn't see you. Come in, come in. Don't touch that — it's a Fireball and it's not in containment yet. Or maybe it is. Hard to tell sometimes. What do you need? Artifacts? Information? Both? Both is good.", hello3:"Do you hear that? That low hum? That's four — no, five — artifacts resonating in my coat pockets. They sing to each other, you know. A Jellyfish and a Stone Blood make a chord in D minor. I documented it all... somewhere. Anyway! What brings you to my humble resonance chamber?", job:"Work? Oh, I always need artifacts. Especially the rare ones — Night Star, Compass, Gold Fish. I'm building a complete periodic table of anomalous matter. Sixty-three specimens catalogued, forty-one to go... or was it forty-two? Numbers get fuzzy after the third Mama's Beads exposure. Bring me artifacts and I'll pay well. Science demands sacrifice — mostly financial, in your case.", anomalies:"Anomalies! My favorite subject. Each one is a window into the Zone's true nature. Whirligigs form along gravitational fault lines — predictable, once you understand the resonance patterns. Burnt Fuzz patches follow emission debris fields. I mapped them all... before the headaches started. Still accurate though. Probably. Bring a detector and don't step where the grass looks too green. That's a Fruit Punch waiting to happen.", information:"Information? I'm a walking encyclopedia, my friend. Did you know that a single Gravi artifact generates enough force to bend a steel beam at twenty centimeters? Or that Eye artifacts actually do improve visual acuity — I wore six of them for a week. My eyesight is perfect now. The tremors are unrelated. Probably. What did you want to know? I was a professor, you know. Before the Zone called.", tips:"Survival tip from a man who carried twelve artifacts at once and lived: lead-lined containers. Not for the artifacts — for your lunch. The radiation gets into everything. Also, never stack Pellicle and Bubble together. The thermal interaction is... educational. I have the scars to prove my thesis. Published it too, in a journal nobody reads anymore because the editorial board is dead. Focus, focus — lead containers. Write it down.", wounded:"*clutching coat pockets* ...the artifacts... don't let them take my artifacts... sixty-three specimens... I catalogued them all... help me and I'll share my research... the periodic table of the Zone... it's almost complete..."},
  "freedom_tentacle_lover": {hello1:"Heyyy brother... *sways* ...you smell like bloodsucker. Got any tentacles on ya? Fresh ones feel alive, y'know? Warm, pulsing... I pay triple — usual price is nothing. Triple! They let me see the real freedom... Zone whispers through 'em, man. I brew 'em light, smoke a bit... suddenly I know where the next emission hides. Don't ask why... just feels right. Got any?", hello2:"Oh man, you again! Tell me you brought something good... something long and wriggly. No? Just browsing? Fine, fine, look around... but if you find a bloodsucker out there, you know who to bring the parts to. Triple pay, always triple. Sit down, have a smoke... not that kind though, heh.", hello3:"*exhales slowly* ...I can feel it, brother. The Zone is breathing today. Bloodsuckers are restless near the warehouses... good for hunting, good for me. You look like a hunter. Bring me tentacles and I'll make it worth your time. Triple the usual. Freedom's finest offer.", job:"Job? Simple, brother... hunt bloodsuckers, bring back their tentacles. Not the whole head, just the good parts — long, wriggly ones. I pay triple, always triple. Why? 'Cause they connect me to the Zone's heartbeat. One puff and I see paths no Duty pig ever finds. Stupid? Maybe. But Freedom ain't about being smart. Bring 'em back, yeah?", anomalies:"Anomalies? Bloodsuckers hide near whirligigs and vortices... tentacles grow stronger there, more sensitive. Bring me some, triple pay. They make me high in the best way — Zone shows me secrets, emissions coming days early, safe routes through mutant packs. I get stupid happy after. Don't laugh, man... try it once.", information:"Info? Only if you bring tentacles first. Triple rubles. I know stuff... because the tentacles talk to me. They tell me where Freedom should expand next, where Monolith hides weak spots. Smoke 'em slow... feel the Zone flow through your veins. Stupid idea? Maybe. But it works. Deal?", tips:"Tip, brother... don't kill bloodsuckers too fast. Let 'em get close — tentacles are best when warm. Cut careful. I pay triple. Brew 'em right and you feel connected. Mutants stop attacking sometimes. Dumb? Yeah. But real freedom. Try it.", wounded:"Ugh... help... you got tentacles? Triple pay... just hand 'em over... need that buzz... Zone calls..."},
  "pers_contractor": {hello1:"State your objective, time window, and extraction plan. Vague requests cost extra.", job:"I take contracts with measurable outcomes. Bring proof, get paid. Bring excuses, get blacklisted.", anomalies:"Plan around anomalies like checkpoints: identify, bypass, confirm. Improvisation is for amateurs and funerals.", information:"I keep verified intel only: source, time, confidence. Rumors are noise unless two channels confirm.", tips:"Tip: if your payment cannot cover your medkit bill, decline the job before your pulse does.", wounded:"I am hit, not finished. Stabilize me and I will still honor the contract."},
  "pers_guide_minded": {hello1:"You look turned around. Before you move, pick landmarks and a retreat line.", job:"I prefer jobs with route discipline: waypoint chain, weather fallback, and night return option.", anomalies:"Anomalies shift with weather and traffic. Re-check old safe lanes after every blowout.", information:"I can trade you path intel: where squads pass, where mutants nest, where radios die.", tips:"Tip: travel edges of open ground. Center routes are fast, but edges keep you alive.", wounded:"Do not stop here. Patch me up and move us to cover before the weather flips."},
  "pers_merc_networker": {hello1:"I keep channels clean and favors cleaner. Reliable people get first call on real work.", job:"Jobs move through trust chains. Finish clean, and I connect you to higher-paying routes.", anomalies:"Anomaly maps age fast. Fresh intel from active couriers is worth more than old PDA dumps.", information:"I track who delivers, who vanishes, and who lies on comms. Network memory never forgets.", tips:"Tip: never brag on open frequency. Reputation grows in whispers, not broadcasts.", wounded:"I can still talk. Get me patched and I will pass your name to my best contacts."},
  "pers_storyteller": {hello1:"Every campfire starts with one lie and one lesson. Ask right, and I will tell you which is which.", job:"A proper job has a route, a fallback, and a witness. If one is missing, the Zone writes the ending for you.", anomalies:"Anomalies repeat patterns before they kill. Watch grass movement, bolt bounce, and the silence between clicks.", information:"Information is memory paid in blood. I trade it, but only with stalkers who listen longer than they speak.", tips:"Tip: mark your return path before your first shot. Most men die on the way back, not on contact.", wounded:"Easy... I still remember the route. Keep me breathing and I will map you a safe way out."},
  "pers_veteran_briefing": {hello1:"You want the short version? Enter with a plan, leave with margin, never chase greed.", job:"Good jobs are boring on paper and profitable in practice. Dramatic jobs fill cemeteries.", anomalies:"Veteran rule: the first bolt is for detection, the second is for confirmation, the third is for trust.", information:"I brief in layers: threat, route, contingency. Skip one, and the Zone collects interest.", tips:"Tip: carry less than your ego wants. Mobility beats inventory every time rounds start flying.", wounded:"Seen worse. Stop the bleeding, then listen: do not fight where you cannot retreat."},
};